Symptom: body mass index (bmi) of 30 or higher
loss of interest in hobbies and activities
chest pain when breathing or coughing
confusion or changes in mental awareness
trouble sleeping due to shortness of breath
but severe cases may include headaches
severe pain in the back or side
itchy roof of mouth or throat
regurgitation of food or sour liquid
sensation of a lump in the throat
drainage down the back of the throat
reduced sense of smell and taste
drainage of fluid from the ear
irritability in infants and young children
a discharge in one or both eyes that forms a crust during the night
a gritty feeling in one or both eyes
itchiness in one or both eyes
redness in one or both eyes
